File: The Department said they are seeing an increase in tests conducted at public laboratories, of the 5 032 tests conducted in the past day, 3 192 were done in public laboratories. JOHANNESBURG - As of Sunday, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 2,173 according to the Health Department. This is an increase of 145 from the previously reported cases. READ: Parliament to meet over COVID-19 fund The total number of tests conducted to date is 80,085. The Department said they are seeing an increase in tests conducted at public laboratories, of the 5 032 tests conducted in the past day, 3 192 were done in public laboratories. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.